Job Description:
HR Coordinator, this is your challenge

Want to make an impact by taking the fast growing international startup Otrium to a higher level when it comes to the employee experience? As an HR Coordinator, together with your colleagues in the People team, you work to contribute to the rapid growth of Otrium with the aim of creating the best working environment. A very diverse hands-on role in which you will further develop HR processes together with your colleagues.
Otrium's mission is that every item of clothing should be worn. With this mission they have become an international online fashion outlet. They ensure that designer brands have the opportunity to find an owner for each item produced.
Do you have a passion for the most efficient HR operations as possible, creating a great culture and would you like to work at one of the fastest growing startups in Europe? This might be your new challenge!

As HR Coordinator you have the following responsibilities:
Supporting the further professionalization and innovation of HR processes;
all occurring activities related to good onboarding, employee engagement, professional development, performance management, data and reports, compensation & benefits, vitality, offboarding and cultural initiatives;
taking care of the personnel and salary administration;
participating in HR projects such as Diversity & Inclusion and Employee Engagement;
point of contact for colleagues when it comes to HR-related matters;
organizing (online) events for employees.
As HR Coordinator you report to the Head of People.

you will take up this challenge at Otrium

“We believe all clothing should be worn”, Otrium was founded based on this mission. At the moment, a lot of fashion remains unsold. A waste of the resources that went into it and for the people who miss it. Otrium is here to solve this problem. An international, online fashion outlet marketplace empowering designer brands to find an owner for every item they produce.
Otrium provides brands with a channel for an online outlet and digital tools to intelligently connect dynamically priced end-of-year collections with fashion lovers. The app redefines outlet shopping, making it easy for customers to find pearls with a lower price. They give fashion a new start at the end of the season: smarter for the wardrobe, smarter for the wallet and smarter for the industry.
You are part of the People team and work closely with the Head of People, Head of Talent Acquisition, another HR Coordinator, the Office Manager and interns. Of course you also want to know what it is like to work here. We can best describe this as follows: a rapidly changing and growing environment with highly motivated colleagues, where hard work and fun go hand in hand. Your organizational skills, eye for detail and ability to set priorities add a lot in this environment.
The office in Amsterdam is easily accessible by car and public transport. Due to Covid-19, work is currently done from home.

the job offers more than a challenge:
Gross monthly salary between € 2.800,- and € 3.200,- per month, depending on your experience;
good fringe benefits such as 25 vacation days and fun (online) events;
the opportunity to work in an enthusiastic and ambitious team with a growth and entrepreneurial mindset;
The possibility to learn, grow, and contribute to one of the fastest-growing startups in Europe, and soon the US (with your help!).
this is what you will bring to the job of HR Coordinator:
HBO or Master degree in HR, Psychology or comparable;
two to four years of experience in the full HR cycle, preferably within a start-up or scale-up;
excellent knowledge on the Dutch employment law.
you like to work hands-on and tactically;
you speak Dutch and English fluently;
you enjoy taking on challenges, you are eager to learn, proactive, independent and you adapt easily in a dynamic environment.
Solliciteren naar de vacature HR Coordinator?

That's great! If your profile matches the job description, we are happy to receive your CV and short motivation. Upload it right away through our website. You can count on an inital response to your application within 5 working days.
Are you new to Rvdb?
When you apply, we immediately create an account for you in RAY. A platform in which you are central. This makes it even easier to find a fantastic job because, for example, all HR vacancies in the Netherlands have been collected.
Note: Because of the new privacy legislations, it is important that you register yourself for RAY. You then agree with our privacy statement. We cannot process CVs and motivations by e-mail.

