Key Responsibilities and Accountabilities:•
Establish a pipeline of new feedstock opportunities;
Assess technical and commercial feasibility of newly presented feedstock options by coordinating with internal stakeholders and external regulatory departments;
Negotiate and close new feedstock supply contracts;
Build and leverage on an international network of individuals, companies and NGO’s that provide valuable information on market and technology;
Support new investment initiatives including new pre-treatment technology;
Liaise closely with internal stakeholders to ensure feedstocks are fit for purpose, sustainable and delivered on time and with the right specifications;
Keep up to date with all relevant legislative drivers within biofuels sector to ensure that Argent are able to exploit market for new sources of feedstock.
Business Development Activities:
Undertake strategic study of all available low cost feedstock materials from waste streams;
Support the trade team by assessing new opportunities that are presented;
Liaise with Sustainability team to ascertain new feedstock status;
Assess and understand the trade-offs for certain types of feedstock that impact biodiesel and by-products (glycerine / waste streams / BFO);
Pursue collaborative trials with customers/suppliers of feedstock. Write trial proposals, project manage trial loads, and write final reports;
Exploit business development opportunities, raising company profile and getting new business contacts within multiple waste industry sectors;
Attend conferences, events, expo’s, shows and presentations to raise company profile, build customer relationships and exploit potential business opportunities;
EU funding/grant applications as appropriate and in conjunction with the Business Support functions.
The Department
The Trading Team is responsible for the purchase of raw materials and chemicals and the sale of products (biodiesel, biofuels, bio-glycerin and bio-fertilisers). The team consists of Head of Trade, 3 (Senior) Traders, Book Manager and 2 Business Development Analysts and this role. The working language in this department is English.
Requirements
You recognize yourself in the following competencies: attention to detail, ambitious, quality-conscious, financially analytical, commercial and a team player.
You also bring:
A completed bachelor / university education (preferably Chemistry or Waste Management) at least 3 years of work experience;
Ideally complemented with a business degree;
Experience with financial and business systems to monitor business activities;
Proven experience preparing and reviewing reports;
Proven ability to work in a commercial culture of continuous improvement, process optimization and intellectual curiosity;
Excellent command of the English language in speech and writing;
Fundamental understanding of fats and oil (wastes) and biodiesel manufacturing processes;
Strong commercial understanding of end to end economics in biodiesel process;
In depth knowledge of waste management sector;
Knowledge of sustainability criteria for biodiesel raw materials;
Strong project management and leadership skills;
Ability to negotiate and sustain networking relationships;
Able to analyse and interpret data.
What do we Offer?
Good primary and secondary employment conditions and an attractive pension scheme;
A bonus scheme based on stated business results;
A Happy Workplace with 350 involved colleagues and lots of room for personal development;
