About PVH Corp.
PVH is one of the most admired fashion and lifestyle companies in the world. We power brands that drive fashion forward – for good. Our brand portfolio includes the iconic CALVIN KLEIN, TOMMY HILFIGER, Van Heusen, IZOD, ARROW, Warner’s, Olga and Geoffrey Beene brands, as well as the digital-centric True&Co. intimates brand. We market a variety of goods under these and other nationally and internationally known owned and licensed brands. PVH has over 40,000 associates operating in over 40 countries and $9.9 billion in annual revenues. That's the Power of Us. That’s the Power of PVH.
The Team
Working in a skilled team with enthusiastic colleagues you will be part of the End User Infrastructure team in close collaboration with the Infrastructure and Network team.
Next to that you will be in close contact with the Digital Transformation team in charge of the Digital Showroom environment.
The team is responsible for implementation of new technologies, support and resolution of incoming incidents and fulfilment of service requests on multiple platforms.
The Position
At PVH we are transforming the fashion industry by breaking conventions every single day. We are always exploring ways to bring the industry forward and constantly accelerating the pace in which we do business. We believe that to succeed as a fashion lifestyle company we need to offer much more than high quality trendy collections. Our goal is to become the ultimate fashion tech brand.
To achieve this, we are looking for an enthusiastic System Engineer who will implement and support the technical infrastructure of our Digital Showroom across the world. Customer value and automation are key in deployment and configuration of our landscape. We are working towards enabling autonomous teams and ‘hands-off’ deployments. In this position you will be an ambassador to both our end-users and local field engineers or third parties so collaboration and maintaining a healthy relationship with adjacent teams is key.
Key Responsibilities:
Maintaining and supporting an environment of Mac and Windows systems;
Designing and implementing management solutions for end-point environments;
Designing and implementing operational models for end-point management solutions (SCCM, Intune);
Communicating and collaborating with multiple global teams involved in supporting the DS environment;
Providing third-line support during selling seasons;
Assisting with roll-outs and upgrades of Digital Showrooms;
Be responsible for content distribution;
Work with our hardware vendors to create a (next gen) hardware setup;
Help debugging software issues;
Automate tasks through SCCM, JAMF and leverage PowerShell for custom automation tasks;
Work with our security department to meet security standards.
The Ideal Candidate:
You have a Bachelor's degree in computer science or equivalent in experience;
Expert knowledge of SCCM/Intune – Design, Implementation and Operational;
PowerShell experience;
Ability and experience as a technical project manager on all phases (Initiate, Plan, Execute, Monitor and Control, Close) to deliver planned work for the DS;
Understanding of networking;
Process based mindset – identify waste and create and implement improvements;
Excellent communication skills and the ability to work with many different stakeholders;
Problem solving mindset;
Agile methodology knowledge and mindset;
You are fluent in the English language;
You can work independently;
You are flexible and able to work under pressure.
What You Can Expect from Us:
A beautiful state-of-the-art Campus, complete with our very own People's Place Gym and People's Place Cafés
A company culture that fosters development, offering training and learning opportunities through our very own PVH University
An international environment which respects diversity, equality, and individuality
A smart work program that empowers our associates to work at their preferred location within a flexible schedule
A chance to unwind with weekly social activities
PVH Europe and our brands, TOMMY HILFIGER and CALVIN KLEIN, are committed to fostering an inclusive and diverse community of associates with a strong sense of belonging. We believe we are bettered by all forms of diversity, and take pride in working with top talent from every walk of life and corner of the world. In the spirit of inclusivity, qualified applicants will be considered without regard to age, ethnicity, ability, gender, gender expression, gender identity, nationality, race, religion or sexual orientation.
